{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Debug Swift code written for Godot in Xcode."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Debugging your SwiftGodot-based extensions using Xcode can either be done with a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"binary Godot executable that you got directly from the Godot project, or using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"your own build of Godot.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Make an Official Godot Engine debuggable","anchor":"Make-an-Official-Godot-Engine-debuggable"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"These steps are only required if you are using an official Godot built.  If you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"compiled your own Godot locally, you do not need to do folow any of these steps."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Download Godot Engine without .Net support version in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/godotengine.org\/download\/macos\/"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"com.apple.security.get-task-allow"},{"type":"text","text":" entitlement and resign it."}]}]}]},{"syntax":"shell","code":["mkdir -p \/tmp\/Godot","cp -R ~\/Downloads\/Godot.app \/tmp\/Godot\/","cd \/tmp\/Godot\/","codesign --display --xml --entitlements Godot.entitlements Godot.app","open Godot.entitlements ","# By default Finder will choose Xcode to open .entitlements file.","# You can open and edit it through any other application which can handle xml.","# Add <key>com.apple.security.get-task-allow<\/key><true\/> in the opened Editor Application","codesign -s - --deep --force --options=runtime --entitlements Godot.entitlements G